obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (43324)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507&sectionId=43324&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Revenue Recovery Act, 1890.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India except ^2[the State of Jammu and Kashmir*];] ^3***`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the India (Adaptation of Income-tax, Profits Tax and Revenue Recovery Acts) Order, 1947 (G.G.O. 31, dated the`
  line `10th December, 1947) (Gazette of India, 1947, Extraordinary, p. 1333), for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 1950, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "Part B States".`
  line
  line `3. The word "and" rep. by Act 10 of 1914, s. 3 and the Second Schedule..`
  line
  line `4. Sub-section (3) rep. by s. 3 and the Second Schedule, ibid.`
  line
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (43325)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507&sectionId=43325&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is something repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(1) "district" includes a presidency-town;`
  line
  line `(2) "Collector" means the chief officer in charge of the land-revenue administration of a district;`
  line and
  line
  line `(3) "defaulter" means a person from whom an arrear of land-revenue, or a sum recoverable as an`
  line `arrear of land-revenue, is due, and includes a person who is responsible as surety for the payment of`
  line `any such arrear or sum.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (43326)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Recovery of public demands by enforcement of processes in other districts than those in which they become payable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1914, s. 2 and the Schedule, Part I.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507&sectionId=43326&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an arrear of land-revenue, or a sum recoverable as an arrear of`
  line `land-revenue, is payable to a Collector by a defaulter being or having property in a district other than that`
  line `in which the arrear accrued or the sum is payable, the Collector may send to the Collector of that other`
  line `district a certificate in the form as nearly as may be of the Schedule, stating--`
  line
  line `(a) the name of the defaulter and such other particulars as may be necessary for his identification,`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) the amount payable by him and the account on which it is due.`
  line
  line `(2) The certificate shall be signed by the Collector making it ^1[or by any officer to whom such`
  line `Collector may, by order in writing, delegate this duty], and, save as otherwise provided by this Act, shall`
  line `be conclusive proof of the matters therein stated.`
  line
  line `(3) The Collector of the other district shall, on receiving the certificate, proceed to recover the`
  line `amount stated therein as if it were an arrear of land-revenue which had accrued in his own district.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Insertion of new section.--After Section 3 of the principal Act, the following shall be inserted as section 3A, namely:--`
  line
  line `“3A.--Certificate Officers to perform the functions of Collector in respect of certificates received.--Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act, when any certificate is received under this Act, by the Collector of a District, any certificate officer in the district may exercise all the powers and perform all the duties and functions of such Collector under this Act, in respect of such certificate.`
  line
  line `Explanation--In this section ‘Certificate Officer’ has the same meaning as in the Bengal Public Demands Recovery Act, 1913 (Bengal Act III of 1913).”`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 16 of 1971, s. 2.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (43327)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Remedy available to person denying liability to pay amount recovered under last foregoing section.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507&sectionId=43327&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) When proceedings are taken against a person under the last foregoing section for the`
  line `recovery of an amount stated in a certificate, that person may, if he denies his liability to pay the amount`
  line `or any part thereof and pays the same under protest made in writing at the time of payment and signed by`
  line `him or his agent, institute a suit for the repayment of the amount or the part thereof so paid.`
  line
  line `(2) A suit under sub-section (1) must be instituted in a Civil Court having jurisdiction in the local area`
  line `in which the office of the Collector who made the certificate is situate, and the suit shall be determined in`
  line `accordance with the law in force at the place where the arrear accrued or the liability for the payment of`
  line `the sum arose.`
  line
  line `(3) In the suit the plaintiff may, notwithstanding anything in the last foregoing section, but subject to`
  line `the law in force at the place aforesaid, give evidence with respect to any matter stated in the certificate.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) This section shall apply if under this Act as in force as part of the law of ^2[Pakistan or] Burma,`
  line `or under any other similar Act forming part of the law of ^2[Pakistan or] Burma, proceedings are taken`
  line `against a person in ^3[Pakistan or Burma, as the case may be,] for the recovery of an amount stated in a`
  line `certificate made by a Collector in ^4[any State to which this Act extends].]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by the A.O.1937.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by the India (Adaptation of Income-tax, Profits Tax and Revenue Recovery Acts) Order, 1941 (G.G.O. 31, dated the 10th`
  line `December, 1947), (Gazette of India, 1947, Extraordinary, p. 1333).`
  line
  line `3. Subs., ibid., for "Burma".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 33 of 1950, s. 2 and the Schedule for "a Part A State or a Part C State".`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (43328)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Recovery by Collectors of sums recoverable as arrears of revenue by other public officers or by local authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507&sectionId=43328&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Where any sum is recoverable as an arrear ,of land-Revenue of any public officer`
  line `other than a Collector or by local authority, the Collector of the district in which the office of that officer`
  line `or authority is situate shall, on the request of the officer or authority, proceed to recover the sum as if it`
  line `were an arrear of land-revenue which had accrued in his own district, and may send a certificate of the`
  line `amount to be recovered to the Collector of another district under the foregoing provisions of this Act, as if`
  line `the sum were payable to himself.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (43329)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Property liable to sale under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507&sectionId=43329&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the Collector of a district receives a certificate`
  line `under this Act, he may issue a proclamation prohibiting the transfer or charging of any immovable`
  line `property belonging to the defaulter in the district.`
  line
  line `(2) The Collector may at any time, by order in writing, withdraw the proclamation, and it shall be`
  line `deemed to be withdrawn when either the amount stated in the certificate has been recovered or the`
  line `property has been sold for the recovery of that amount.`
  line
  line `(3) Any private alienation of the property or of any interest of the defaulter therein, whether by sale,`
  line `gift, mortgage or otherwise, made after the issue of the proclamation and before the withdrawal thereof,`
  line `shall be void as^1[against the ^2[Government]] and any person who may purchase the property at a sale`
  line `held for the recovery of the amount stated in the certificate.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the foregoing provisions of this section, when proceedings are taken against any`
  line `immovable property under this Act for the recovery of an amount stated in a certificate, the interest of the`
  line `defaulter alone therein shall be so proceeded against, and no incumbrances created, grants made or`
  line `contracts entered into by him in ^3good faith shall be rendered invalid by reason only of proceedings being`
  line `taken against those interests.`
  line
  line `(5) A proclamation under this section shall be made by beat of drum or other customary method and`
  line `by the posting of a copy thereof on a conspicuous place in or near the property to which it relates.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A O. 1937, for "against the Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "Crown".`
  line
  line `3. See definition in the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), s. 22.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (43330)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Saving of local laws relating to revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507&sectionId=43330&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in the foregoing sections shall be construed--`
  line
  line `(a) to impair any security provided by, or affect the provisions of, any other enactment for the`
  line `time being in force for the recovery of land-revenue or of sums recoverable as arrears of landrevenue, or`
  line
  line `(b) to authorise the arrest of any person for the recovery of any tax payable to the corporation,`
  line `commissioner, committee, board, council or person having authority over a municipality under any`
  line `enactment for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (43331)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Recovery in India of certain public demands arising beyond India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507&sectionId=43331&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `When this Act has been`
  line `applied to any local area which is under the administration of ^1[the Central Government ^2***] but which`
  line `is not part of ^3[`
  line `^4*** India], an arrear of land-revenue accruing in that local area, or a sum recoverable as`
  line `an arrear of land-revenue and payable to a Collector or other public officer or to a local authority in that`
  line `local area, may be recovered under this Act in ^3[`
  line `^4*** India].`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the G. G. in C.".`
  line
  line `2. The words "or the Crown Representative" omitted by the India (Adaptation of Income-tax, Profits Tax and Revenue Recovery`
  line `Acts) Order, 1947 (G. G. O. 31, dated the 10th December, 1947) (Gazette of India, 1947, Extraordinary, p. 1333).`
  line
  line `3. Subs., ibid., for "British India".`
  line
  line `4. The words "the Provinces of" omitted by the A.O.1950.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (43332)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Recovery in India of land revenues etc., accruing in Burma.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507&sectionId=43332&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Recovery in India of land revenues, etc., accruing in Burma.--(1) The Central Government`
  line `may direct^2`
  line `that an arrear of land-revenue accruing in Burma or a sum recoverable in Burma as an arrear`
  line `of land-revenue and payable to a Collector or other public officer or to a local authority in Burma may be`
  line `recovered under this Act in ^3*** India and thereupon such arrear or sum shall be so recoverable:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall not give any such direction unless it is satisfied that the`
  line `remedy available under section 4 of this Act in ^3*** India to a person paying under protest in ^3*** India`
  line `an arrear accruing in ^3*** India is available under Burma law in Burma to a person paying under protest`
  line `in ^3*** India an arrear accruing in Burma.`
  line
  line `(2) For recovering by virtue of this section any arrears of tax, penalty due under the enactments`
  line `relating to income-tax or super-tax in force in Burma, the Collector shall have such additional powers as`
  line `he has in the case of Indian income-tax and super-tax under the proviso to section 46(2) of the Income-tax`
  line `Act, 1922 (11 of 1922).`
  line
  line `^4[(3) Sub-sections (1) and (2) shall apply in relation to Pakistan as they apply in relation to Burma.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by the A. O. 1937.`
  line
  line `2. For a direction under this section, see Gazette of India, 1937, Pt. I, p. 1941.`
  line
  line `3. The word "British" omitted by the India (Adaptation of Income-tax, Profits Tax and Revenue Recovery Acts) Order, 1947`
  line `(G.G.O.31, dated the 10th December, 1947) (Gazette of India, 1947, Extraordinary, p. 1333).`
  line
  line `4. Ins., ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (43333)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Duty of Collectors to remit moneys collected in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Ins., ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507&sectionId=43333&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00035_189001_1523274075507
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Where a Collector receives a`
  line `certificate under this Act from, a Collector of another State or a Collector in ^1[Pakistan or] Burma, he`
  line `shall remit any sum recovered by him by virtue of that certificate to that Collector, after deducting his`
  line `expenses in connection with the matter.]`
